# ADR-010 Completion Report — Public API Contract Migration

## Status: ✅ Complete

## Overview

ADR-010 required that all Application Response DTOs use only primitive types (`Guid`, `string`, `decimal`, `int`, `List<T>`) instead of Domain Value Objects, Domain Enums, Money, or Domain Collections. All 5 modules have been migrated.

## Summary Statistics

| Metric | Count |
|--------|-------|
| **Modules migrated** | 5 (Catalog, Tables, Orders, Kitchen, Payments) |
| **DTOs migrated or verified** | 9 |
| **Value Objects removed from Public API** | 14 (`*Id` types) |
| **Enums converted to `string`** | 9 (`TableStatus`, `OrderStatus`, `ProductStatus`, `ProductVisibility`, `ProductCategoryStatus`, `IngredientStatus`, `KitchenTicketStatus`, `PaymentStatus`, `PaymentMethod`) |
| **Money fields converted to `decimal`** | 7 (3 in Product, 2 in OrderItem/OrderResponseV2, 3 in Payment) |
| **Collections flattened from `IReadOnlyCollection<T>` to `List<T>`** | 4 |
| **Quantity fields converted to `int`** | 1 (`Quantity`) |

